ws were published in the Sunday edition of the Pittsburgh Press, and are mainly of books about theater but include some contemporary fiction and literary criticism.  The original clippings have been xeroxed.</p></scopecontent><c02 id="aspace_ref62_5i7" level="file"><did><unittitle>Book reviews</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1961/1965" type="inclusive">1961-1965</unitdate><container id="aspace_d990a2c6f3f395a6e98a25c464fb59b8" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">5</container><container id="aspace_30688017457d26bb04298141f2543606" parent="aspace_d990a2c6f3f395a6e98a25c464fb59b8" type="folder">8</container></did></c02><c02 id="aspace_ref63_zva" level="file"><did><unittitle>Book reviews</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1966/1974" type="inclusive">1966-1974</unitdate><container id="aspace_4ed89c74f2e1e85e1f8098a031d0ed26" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">5</container><container id="aspace_64578f64c535879a2703111601756323" parent="aspace_4ed89c74f2e1e85e1f8098a031d0ed26" type="folder">9</container></did></c02><c02 id="aspace_ref65_qof" level="file"><did><unittitle>Book reviews - no dates</unittitle><container id="aspace_b0eacce1caaa253050d6b672e9568d63" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">5</container><container id="aspace_e1cd5490b0eb2721f80c543c3227bef9" parent="aspace_b0eacce1caaa253050d6b672e9568d63" type="folder">10</container></did></c02></c01><c01 id="aspace_ref66_8z9" level="series"><did><unittitle>Legal Documents and Miscellaneous Materials</unittitle><unitid>IV.</unitid></did><scopecontent id="aspace_23d443f96489a9a8128c2e500225d415"><head>Scope and Content Notes</head><p>Series includes legal materials, employment records, photographs, etc.  The scrapbook covers Peter Gregg's acting career.  It includes Carnegie Tech, Off-Broadway, and Broadway programs, photographs, Equity Contracts, clippings, etc.  Also contains several Pittsburgh articles that summarize Gregg's years in New York.  There are two tape recordings of a Pittsburgh Ad Club production, <title render="italic">Ad Cats and Goose Livers</title>, written by Mr. Gregg.  Also includes programs from the Ad Club, Lemonade Opera, and some material relating to Mr. Gregg's radio days.  There are several newsletters and other publications from the Dramatist's Guild, The Lions Club of Pittsburgh, and the Pittsburgh Ad Club.</p></scopecontent><c02 id="aspace_ref6_a3n" level="series"><did><unittitle>Personal history and resumes</unittitle><container id="aspace_419fa64a1588a5e756a875d018bfdeaa" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">6</container><container id="aspace_e7e5dcb841aa91fc7fed5b6f45c562d7" parent="aspace_419fa64a1588a5e756a875d018bfdeaa" type="folder">1</container></did></c02><c02 id="aspace_ref67_39h" level="file"><did><unittitle>Copyrights</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1946/1950" type="inclusive">1946-1950</unitdate><container id="aspace_461b3cd69db69c348dce23d1b1ccfa19" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">6</container><container id="aspace_4cdc7463a2502b375c13d8bd47838590" parent="aspace_461b3cd69db69c348dce23d1b1ccfa19" type="folder">2</container></did></c02><c02 id="aspace_ref68_wvw" level="file"><did><unittitle>Theatrical contracts</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1947/1953" type="inclusive">1947-1953</unitdate><container id="aspace_5cb05e2886636df3d5063ed1a6f52b5d" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">6</container><container id="aspace_814faa05c9938eb60df25e60c311749f" parent="aspace_5cb05e2886636df3d5063ed1a6f52b5d" type="folder">3</container></did></c02><c02 id="aspace_ref69_i0l" level="file"><did><unittitle>Employment records</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1946/1954" type="inclusive">1946-1954</unitdate><container id="aspace_a4acd53a74d20757d9dfe14931a7622c" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">6</container><container id="aspace_b1b21d14c4c5e0da2111f531dba0d143" parent="aspace_a4acd53a74d20757d9dfe14931a7622c" type="folder">4</container></did></c02><c02 id="aspace_ref70_sas" le